urls.title: Color of Hockey: Janda making inroads on Canucks radio broadcasts
urls.description: William Douglas has been writing The Color of Hockey blog since 2012. Douglas joined NHL.com in 2019 and writes about people of color in the sport. Today, he profiles Randip Janda, a Vancouver Canucks broadcaster who is the NHL's first fulltime radio color commentator of South Asian heritage.

data.text:
“There are individuals that look like me on a broadcast. It does motivate you. It does show that there's a place for us in the game."

Changing the game for the better. Keep inspiring, @RandipJanda.

READ | https://t.co/OUx61aWIak https://t.co/DtN80lnzN1
